ONCE: per computer: 
   1.  Settings → Developer Settings → Personal Access Token
                    → Generate New Token (Give your password) → Enter date and
                      → Add all permissions and fill form → click Generate token
                       → SAVE *** Token ***
    2. Copy token into a "Windows Credential"
        Control Panel → Credential Manager → Add Windows Credentials → URL: git:https://github.com 
                     → Password <= *** Token ***

For each "Repo"

1.  Create Your new GiHub (remote) repo

3. CMD 
   CD to <Your local repo> (    git init; git add . ;  git commit;  git commit    ......)
   git remote add origin https://github.com/<Your-GitHubUser>/<Repo>.git
(Change "origin" to "main")
   git branch -M main
   git push -u origin main
   or 
   git remote add --mirror=push origin https://github.com/shomrai/<Your-Repo>.git
Check Your target repo in Github:
   git remote -v
  